  "issue_number": 223,
  "issue_title": "Feature: parse Skills v2 metadata",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\n`SkillStore` currently parses skills with ad hoc Markdown scanning. After the Skills v2 schema is documented, TouchPilot needs structured parsing and clear malformed-skill errors.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd richer skill models and update `SkillStore` to parse the v2 metadata fields. The parser should preserve Markdown instructions, expose structured metadata, and report invalid required fields or invalid tool names clearly.\n\n## User workflow\n\nWhen TouchPilot starts, bundled skills load into structured models. Broken skill files should be diagnosable from tests and developer logs instead of silently losing important metadata.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nStructured local parsing gives the agent, UI, and policy layers a reliable on-device source of skill knowledge.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nThe parser must not silently accept malformed allowlists or unknown risk values. Invalid skill metadata should fail closed for policy-sensitive fields.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\nParsing only headings/lists would preserve current behavior, but it would not support Milestone 6 matching, examples, risk, or success criteria.\n\n## Order note\n\nThis is PR 2 of 9. It depends on the schema/docs issue and should land before registry, matching, UI details, bundled skill upgrade, and policy integration.",
